Title: Declaration of Artistic Property Rights Against Digital Submission and Sharing

This petition calls for a declaration of artistic property rights against digital submission and sharing of proprietary content. The text follows:

Petition for Legal Definition and Characterization of Unauthorized Digital Reproduction and Subsequent Public Dissemination of Proprietary Content:

WHEREAS, Art reproduction has been a means of self-expression since the earliest days of artistic craftsmanship, and the sale of an artwork or exhibition of an artwork constitutes a form of dissemination;
WHEREAS, artificial intelligence and digital technology have transformed our artistic landscape, enabling self-publishing, digital creation, and exploration of new forms of artistic expression;
WHEREAS, unauthorized digital reproduction and subsequent public dissemination, by unauthorized individuals, of works of art, except for fair use, violate the copyright laws of the United States and internationally;

NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED, That citizens of the United States of America, legislative and representative bodies, and privately owned libraries of all nations bind themselves to uphold the principles of fair use and artistic property rights against defamation of character, literal infringement or copying of third-party material, and intentional material alteration in the context of just, fair and beneficial arguments of artistic practice.

The Petitioner hereby takes sole responsibility for the legality, legitimacy, and consequences of their initiative, without relying on the support or aid of any individual or entity. Furthermore, the Petitioner ultimately reserves the right to refile or pursue any claims of infringement against any third party who has violated their rights in the context of self-expression and artistic expression.

Given under digital signatures of Puppeteer Petitioner Judge on 2/2/2021.
